            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Hd1e108">Rubrica 2</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De inuidia: zelo et nemessatione</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e114">
              De inuidia 
              <lb ed="#K" n="16"/>zelo et nemessatione Rubrica 2
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e119">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref>Iob histo c 2</ref> <quote>paruulum 
              <lb ed="#K"/>occidit inuidia</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e126">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e123">Salomon in eccl c 8</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e130">Ait salomon contempla<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>tus
              sum omnes labores hominum 
              <lb ed="#K"/>et industrias animaduerti patere in<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>uidie 
              proximi</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e139">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e138">Aristoteles rethori li 2 c 12</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e143">Ne messare est tristari 
              <lb ed="#K"/>de eo qui videtur indigne bene agere</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e151">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e150">c 13</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e153">Inuidia est tristitia quedam 
              <lb ed="#K"/>super bona actione apparente bo<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>norum 
              circa similes /Inuidebunt ta<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>les 
              quibus sunt aliqui similes aut 
              <lb ed="#K"/>videntur Amatores honoris 
              <lb ed="#K"/>magis inuidiosi sunt quam non 
              <lb ed="#K"/>amatores honoris et opinati sapientes sunt 
              <lb ed="#K"/>vniuersaliter amatores fame 
              <lb ed="#K"/>circa aliquid inuidiosi sunt contra 
              <lb ed="#K"/>hoc</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e176">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e179">14 c</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e180">Zelus est tristitia que<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>dam 
              super apparenti potentia Bo<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>norum 
              honorabilium et contingen<lb ed="#K" n="1" break="no"/>tium
                  <pb ed="#K" n="73-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#K" n="a"/>
              <lb ed="#K"/>sibi accipere praeter similes natura 
              <lb ed="#K"/>non quia alii sed quia non et 
              <lb ed="#K"/>sibi sunt zelatiuus seipsum prae<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>parat 
              propter emulationem vt 
              <lb ed="#K"/>obtineat bona /Inuidus autem vt pro<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>ximus 
              non habeat proptur inui<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>diam 
              necesse est zelatiuos quidem 
              <lb ed="#K"/>esse dignificantes seipsos bo<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>nis
              que non habent / Iuuenes et m<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>agnanimi 
              sunt zelatiui</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e201"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e208">Idem 
              <lb ed="#K"/>topicorum libro 2</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e203">Inuidia est tristitia
              <lb ed="#K"/>in apparenti vtilitate alicuius</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e211">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e223">Iesus filius sirach in eccl c 9</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e215">Non 
              <lb ed="#K"/>zeles gloriam et opes peccatoris 
              <lb ed="#K"/>non enim scis que futura sit il<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>lius 
              subuersio</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e223">
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e235">30 c</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e225">Zelus et
               <lb ed="#K"/>iracundia minuunt dies</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e232">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e248">Oratius in epistolis 2 c</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e236">Inui<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>dus 
              alterius macrescit rebus 
              <lb ed="#K"/>optimis</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e242">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e260">Tullius de oratore li 2</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e246">Laudi atque glorie maxime 
              <lb ed="#K"/>inuideri solet Inuident homines 
              <lb ed="#K"/>maxime paribus aut inferioribus 
              <lb ed="#K"/>inuident sepe vehementer et eo 
              <lb ed="#K"/>magis si intolerantius seiac<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>tant 
              et equabilitatem communis iuris 
              <lb ed="#K"/>praestantia dignitatis aut for<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>tune 
              sue transeunt plerique sunt 
              <lb ed="#K"/>inuidi maximeque commune hoc 
              <lb ed="#K"/>est vitium Inuidetur praestanti 
              <lb ed="#K"/>florentique fortune vt hoc opinio 
              <lb ed="#K"/>minuatur et illa excellens op<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>pinione 
              fortuna cum laboribus 
              <lb ed="#K"/>et miseriis permixta videatur</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e271">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e289">Idem tusculanarum quaestionem li 3</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e273">Inuiden<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>tia 
              egritudo est ex alterius rebus secundis</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e281">
                  <cb ed="#K" n="b"/>
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e301">Idem philippicorum libro 9</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e283">Nemo al<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>terius
              qui sue confidit virtuti inuidet</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e289">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e311">Idem de essentia mundi</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e291">Probus 
              <lb ed="#K"/>nemini inuidet</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e297">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e324">Ouidius sine titulo seu amorum libro i c 15 et fi</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e301">Pa<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>scitur 
              in inuidis liuor post fata quiscit Tunc si vis ex 
              <lb ed="#K"/>merito quemque tuetur homo</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e310">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e338">Idem 
              <lb ed="#K"/>de arte amandi li i</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e314">Fertilior se<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>ges 
              est alienis semper in agris 
              <lb ed="#K"/>Uicinumque pecus grandius vber 
              <lb ed="#K"/>habet</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e322">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e351">Idem de remedio amoris 
              <lb ed="#K"/>li i contra fi</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e326">Summa petit liuor 
              <lb ed="#K"/>perflant altissima venti summa 
              <lb ed="#K"/>petunt dextera fulmina missa iouis</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e334">
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e364">Idem de fastis li 4</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e338">Que non 
               <lb ed="#K"/>liuor adit</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e342">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e374">Idem de poento li 3 e 3</ref> 
              <lb ed="#K"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e346">Liuor iners vicium mores non 
              <lb ed="#K"/>exit in altos Utque latens ima 
              <lb ed="#K"/>vipera serpit humo</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e360">
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e393">Epistola 4</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e364">Scrip<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>ta 
               placent a morte fere que 
               <lb ed="#K"/>ledere viuos Liuor et iniusto car<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>pore 
               dente solet</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e372">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e405">Lib 4 et fi epistola 16 
              <lb ed="#K"/>et fi</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e374">non solet ingeniis summa no<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>cere 
              dies famaque post cineres 
              <lb ed="#K"/>maior venit</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e383">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e419">Quintilianus declamationum 12 declam</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e387">Quo non pene<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>trans 
              improbe liuor quidue scabre 
              <lb ed="#K"/>malignitati clausum est</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e395">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e432">Mattheus in euangelio c 13</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e399">Non est propheta 
              <lb ed="#K"/>sine honore nisi in patria sua et in cognatione sua et in domo sua</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e407">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e446">Marcus in euangel. c. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e411">Non est propheta
        sine honore nisi in patria sua: et in cognatio
        ne sua et in domo sua.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e419">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e460">Lucas in euange. c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e423">Nemo propheta acce
        ptus est in patria sua.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e429">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e472">Ioannes in euange. c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e433">Propheta in sua pa
        tria honorem non habet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e439">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e484">Paulus apostolus epstola ad galathas. c. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e443">Si in
        uicem mordetis et comeditis: videte ne ab
        inuicem consumamini.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e452">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e499">Seneca tragediarum in hercule furente. c. 3</ref>
        <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e456">Inuidia fastum ac sermo popularis premet.
        Arx praemi regni est posse ab inuidia pati.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e464">
               /
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e512">Idem epistolarum ad lucillum li. 14. e. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e468">Nemo eo
        rum qui in re publica versantur quos vincant
        sed a quibus vincantur aspicit: et illis non tam iocun
        dum est multos post se videre quam graue est
        aliquem ante se habere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e480">
            <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e528">Idem de consolatione
        ad paulinum.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e482">Edax et inimica est semper alienis
        profectibus inuidia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e490">
            <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e541">Idem de tranquillitate
        animi:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e492">Alit liuorem infelix inertia: et omnes de
        strui cupiunt qui se prouehere non possunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e500">
       <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e554">Idem
        de breuitate vite:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e502">In vicino versatur inuidia.
        Simplicius longe posita miramur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e510">
            <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e567">Idem in
        prouerb.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e512">Inuidia est dolor animi ex alienis com
        modis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e521">
               
                <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e583">Lucanus li. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e525">Abscidit nostre multum sors
        inuida laudi.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e531">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e595">Iuuenalis lib. 4. satura i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e535">Quosdam precipitat
        subiecta potentia magne Inuidie.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e541">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e607">Marcialis cocus epigramaton lib. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e545">Esse
        quid dicam quod viuis fama negatur.
        Et sua quod rarus tempora lector amat.
        Hi sunt inuidie nimirum regule mores. <!--113.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  Preferat antiquos semper vt illa nouis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e562">
               /
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e630">Idem li. vndique suscepto. c. i.</ref>
         <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e566">Inuidus irrisor rediuiuo crimine gaudet.
        Et semel irrisum: terque quaterque cupit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e574">
               
               / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e644">Cap. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e578">Inuidie flammam qui tigiline laboras:
        Exiccata cutis omnibus insinuat.
        Torres inuidia non quintum candide: sed te
        Tores inuidia: non alium nisi te.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e588">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e660">Ualerius max. li. 4. ti. de amore et dilctione</ref>
         <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e592">Nulla tam modesta felicitas est que mali
        gnitatis dentes vitare possit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e601">
               
                <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e675">Priscianus li. 18. et fi. ti.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e605">de significatione
        verborum significantium actionem et transitionem.<!--add to ref?-->
        Inuideo tibi: quasi non inuidens tibi fio: hoc
        est non ferens te bene agentem videre.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e615">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e693">Boetius in li. diuisionum:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e619">Quicquid nouum
        est in pudenti obstinatione obliqui mors ob
        tractionis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e627">
            <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e705">Idem de disciplina scholarium
        li. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e629">Inuidia si secundum quid aduenerit: videli
        cet in discendo gratuita est. Simpliciter vero pro
        prii est auctoris consumptura.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e639">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e722">Cassiodorus epistolarum li. i. e. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e643">Quicquid
        ex inuidia dicitur veritas non putatur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e649">
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e732">Lib. 6.
        epistola. 22.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e651">Maiori cura tractanda sunt veni in
        uidia plus timetur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e659">
            <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e745">Libro. 10. e. 11.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e661">Profe
        ctibus quidem proxima est indubitanter inuidia
        Inuidia tolerantia melius vincitur: que con
        tentione semper augetur:</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e672">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e762">Gregorius in pastorali. c. 35.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e676">Inuidi dum
        liuorem a corde non proiiciunt ad apertas
        operum nequitias deuoluuntur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e684">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e776">Auctor lib. qui dicitur pamphilus. c. 25.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e688">Omnia
        non cessat carpere liuor edax.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e694">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e788">Mattheus vindocinensis in poetria: parte
        2. et fi. c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e698">Fascinat inuidie: spiritus omne bonum
        Inuidia est odium aliene infelicitatis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e706">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e803">Gaufridus in poetria. c. 18.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e710">Pessima res
        liuor: totus letale venenum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e716">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e815">Iacobus beneuentanus. c. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e720">Ut durum fer
        rum mordax consumit erugo.
        Sic hominis lacerat intima liuor edax.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-d1e728">
               
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Rd1e829">Prouerb. vulgar.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d32659-Qd1e732">Cane en cosina so par
        non de sira.</quote>
            </p>
